  (text_box "Keep power and analog ground planes seperate. This ensures no high frequency noise from the inverter disrupts sensors and ICs. Only connect at a single point using star configuration. Make sure no power loops cross into other plane when routing."
    (at 125.73 101.6 0) (size 21.59 31.75)
    (stroke (width 0) (type default))
    (fill (type none))
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid 1f923792-8d34-4d35-ae75-366ad0ad7047)
  )
  (text_box "Bus Capacitance Calculation:\nC_{Bulk,min} > I_{ripple} / f_{PWM} / V_{ripple}\n=> C_{Bulk,min} > p_{ripple, I}*I_{Motor} / (f_{PWM} * p_{ripple, V} * V_{Supply})\n\n\nFor 35A, 35V Input and 25kHz Switching Frequency \n(using suggested Variances from TI Application Note):\nC_{Bulk,min} > 10% * 15A / (25kHz * 1% * 35V) = 172uF\n\n\nScale Factor k = 3\nC_{Bulk} = k * C_{Bulk,min}\nC_{Bulk} = 3 * 172uF = 514uF  \n"
    (at 24.13 140.97 0) (size 139.7 53.34)
    (stroke (width -0.0001) (type default) (color 0 0 0 1))
    (fill (type none))
    (effects (font (size 2.5 2.5) (color 0 0 0 1)) (justify left top))
    (uuid 3dde42ed-8cf8-4cd0-b959-84c8857d94de)
  )

  (text "NetTie of Analog and Power Ground Planes" (at 92.71 97.79 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.5 1.5) (thickness 0.3) bold) (justify left bottom))
    (uuid 0ec94813-427b-427b-a54b-69aeaeab650d)
